medical_history.chief_complaint: 7 cm right multicystic mass in the ovary.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: At age 23, a fast-growing abdominal mass was detected ultrasonographically, leading to laparotomy and subsequent diagnosis of a multifocal intrafollicular granulosa cell tumor.
medical_history.past_medical_history: History of multiple tumors including telangiectatic osteosarcoma, malignant and typical phyllodes tumors, reticulohistiocytoma of the skin, breast carcinomas, lipo- and leiomyosarcoma, myometrial leiomyomas, and early endometrial carcinoma.
medical_history.family_history: No history of tumors in family members; all relatives had wild-type p53.
